  "title": "The Empire's Tender Care",
  "summary": "Captured after a raid and patched up by the medical staff aboard the Inquisitor, the Rebel Shael wakes strapped to an operating slab in an ISB interrogation chamber, addressed only as Prisoner C-1125. A cold, methodical Internal Security Bureau agent named Dreven informs her that her identity has been erased and demands she explain her terrorist actions against the Empire. When her defiant answers fail to satisfy him, Dreven calmly cuts open her arms one by one and screws painful electrified orbs into the wounds, promising five in total. Shael clings to the desperate hope that Krieg or Skywalker will come to rescue her, hurling insults and even demanding to see Inrokana, but the agent reminds her she is beyond help within ISB hold. After she refuses to cooperate, Dreven activates the devices, subjecting her to excruciating electric shocks until she screams and finally falls unconscious.",
